    (E'Birdcage', E'Bethnal Green', E'80 Columbia Road\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 7QB', E'Operated by Brewdog. This ex Truman''s pub has a more traditional feel than their other outlets. Food is focused around pies.', 51.5284, -0.071049, E'(020) 3206 1970', E'https://placekitten.com/403/303'),
    (E'Camel', E'Bethnal Green', E'277 Globe Road\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 0JD', E'Good little pub. Usual range of reals includes a gold, Sambrooks Wandle. Snug in Winter. Lots of outdoor pavement space  Famous for specialty pies and toasties,food is served until 9pm.  South facing beer garden. With interesting decor the pub is frequently used as a film set. Minimum Card spend is £5 [Feb 25]', 51.5289, -0.05211, E'07305 470811', E'https://placekitten.com/404/304'),
    (E'Carpenter''s Arms', E'Bethnal Green', E'73 Cheshire Street\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 6EG', E'Former Truman''s street-corner pub, tastefully refurbished and popular with the young Shoreditch and Bethnal Green crowd. Pictures on the wall show historical views of the pub and the local area. An opening at the rear of the front bar leads to two back rooms, the garden and smoking area, and the toilets. A small selection of Belgian bottled beers is available highlighting Lambic beers. There is usually a cider on handpump in the summer. replacing one of the cask ales. Eleven beers on tap. Cashless Venue.', 51.524, -0.0673508, NULL, E'https://placekitten.com/400/300'),
    (E'Dundee Arms', E'Bethnal Green', E'339 Cambridge Heath Road\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 9LH', E'Reopened on a free of tie Lease on 2 April 2015. A sister pub to the crooked Billet. There is a mixture of wood paneling (both painted and unpainted) and bare brick walls. A wonderful and very rare original mosaic sign "Dundee Arms" was uncovered during the refurbishment. Likely to be late Victorian. Otherwise mostly distressed interior with some comfortable fixed bench seating. Opposite the York Hall where the Pigs Ear Beer Festival was founded in 1983. Main toilets are upstairs.', 51.5293, -0.056027, E'(020) 7729 6903', E'https://placekitten.com/401/301'),
