    (E'Hare', E'Bethnal Green', E'505 Cambridge Heath Road\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 9BU', E'Ex-Truman, now a free house. Determinedly ungentrified pub, which nevertheless is very popular with both older East End custom and more bohemian incomers to the area. Former horseshoe bar, now moved back to provide more space, but still not spacious. Sky TVs, pool, darts, varied jukebox, small covered heated rear courtyard for smokers, well fed white cat in residence.', 51.5334, -0.057436, E'(020) 7613 0519', E'https://placekitten.com/403/303'),
    (E'Kings Arms', E'Bethnal Green', E'11a Buckfast Street\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 6EY', E'This pub serves up to 6 cask ales. This pub was taken over in 2013 and refurbished with a mixture of dark green panelling and contemporary Tiling. About 50 bottled beers from the UK,Scandanavia and the US are served. An ever changing range of keg beers..Food is scotch eggs  together with cheese and meat boards. Pub was taken over in November 2024 and is now the sister pub of the Sutton Arms in Clerkenwell.', 51.5257, -0.06582, E'(020) 7729 2627', E'https://placekitten.com/404/304'),
    (E'Marksman', E'Bethnal Green', E'254 Hackney Road\n\nBethnal Green\n\nE2 7SJ', E'1860s pub. Formerly tied to West brewery, later to Hoare, Charrington, but a free house since the 1970s. Décor blends contemporary and period features, e.g. an octagonal skylight at the front, chandeliers made from drinks bottles. Mix of newer and longer-standing East End custom.\n\nNamed Michelin "Pub of the Year" for 2017.', 51.5309, -0.069505, E'(020) 7739 7393', E'https://placekitten.com/400/300'),
